text.section:
Subject to subsection (b) of this section, the governing body of a county may adopt an ordinance, resolution, or regulation or take any other action that the governing body considers necessary to authorize a person to:
Use the person's personal property or real estate to operate a seafood business;
Buy or sell seafood;
Store equipment used in the person's seafood business;
Enjoy the quiet conduct of the person's seafood business in conformance with county and State requirements; and
Harvest seafood.
